            "title": "",
            "content": "<h3><strong>At 37, I gave it all up for a hair clip.</strong></h3><p><strong>And it's the best decision I've ever made.</strong></p><h5><strong>A morning like any other.</strong></h5><p>My name is Laura. I'm a mum, an entrepreneur, and like so many women, my days start at full speed. That morning, like every other, I quickly put my hair up with a regular clip. Then, in the car, head against the headrest — that pain. That hard point pressing into my skull. Again.</p><p>And for the first time, I asked myself the question: why, in 2025, do we still put up with this?</p>",
