        "image_azLjGG": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Capture_d_ecran_2026-05-12_a_12.30.54.png",
            "media_width": 50,
            "media_position": "end",
            "text_position": "place-self-center text-center",
            "icon": "none",
            "icon_width": 48,
            "subheading": "",
            "title": "",
            "content": "<h3><strong>125 years and nobody changed a thing.</strong></h3><p>When I started looking into it, I found something that shocked me: the hair clip was invented in 1901. Same spring. Same mechanism. Same discomfort. For 125 years, nobody had changed anything. Nobody had thought to do better. So I decided to do it myself.</p><p>We worked. A lot. Failed versions, tests, adjustments. Until the day I held the right one in my hands. Two parts. Magnets. A flat, lightweight, comfortable clip. Designed for women's real days — in the car, at the gym, at the office, on the sofa. No pain. No compromise.</p><p>The first women who tested it all said the same thing:</p><p><em>\"But… why didn't this exist before?\"</em></p><p>That's when I knew we had something big.</p>",
            "link_text": "",
            "link_url": "",
            "background": "#ffffff",
            "background_gradient": "",
            "text_color": "#1a1a1a",
            "text_gradient": "",
            "button_background": "",
            "button_text_color": ""
